                        </a></div></div><ol class="senses_multiple" htag="ol"><span class="shcut-g" id="accept_sngs_1"> <h2 class="shcut" htag="h2" id="accept_shcut_1" hclass="shcut">offer/invitation</h2><li class="sense" id="accept_sng_1" hclass="sense" cefr="a2" ox3000="y" htag="li" sensenum="1"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><div class="symbols" hclass="symbols" htag="div"><a href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/wordlists/oxford3000-5000?dataset=english&amp;list=ox3000&amp;level=a2"><span class="ox3ksym_a2"> </span></a></div></span> <span class="grammar" hclass="grammar" htag="span">[intransitive, transitive]</span> <span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">to take willingly something that is offered; to say ‘yes’ to an offer, invitation, etc.</span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">He asked me to marry him and I accepted.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"> <span class="cf" htag="span" hclass="cf">accept something</span> <span class="x">Please accept our sincere apologies.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">It was pouring with rain so I <span class="cl">accepted his offer</span> of a lift.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">I am unfortunately unable to <span class="cl">accept your</span> kind <span class="cl">invitation</span>.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">The board of directors <span class="cl">accepted our proposal</span>.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">She's decided not to accept the job.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">Please accept this small token of my appreciation.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"> <span class="cf" hclass="cf" htag="span">accept something from somebody</span> <span class="x">He is charged with accepting bribes from a firm of suppliers.</span></li><li class="" htag="li"> <span class="cf" hclass="cf" htag="span">accept something for something</span> <span class="x">